<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Sparrow</strong></span> lives in Phoenicia, New York, where he makes small paper sculptures that most people would call “garbage pasted onto garbage.” He has two forthcoming books: a novella, <em>The Princeton Diary</em>, and a collection of essays, <em>Small Happiness &amp; Other Epiphanies</em>. You can follow him on Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/sparrow14">@Sparrow14</a>. But don’t vote for him.</p><a href="/contributors/sparrow" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;▸</a>		</div>
